History[edit]




SanDisk founders: Jack Yuan, Eli Harari, and Sanjay Mehrotra (2010).


SanDisk was founded in 1988 by Dr. Eli Harari, Sanjay Mehrotra and Jack Yuan.[4] SanDisk co-founder Dr. Eli Harari developed the Floating Gate EEPROM which proved the practicality, reliability and endurance of semiconductor-based data storage.[5]
Acquisitions[edit]

In October 2005, Sandisk acquired Matrix Semiconductor.[6]
In July 2006, SanDisk acquired M-Systems.[7]
In May 2011, SanDisk acquired Pilant Technology, a manufacturer of solid state drives, for US$327 million.[8]
In February 2012, SanDisk acquired FlashSoft.[9]
In June 2012, SanDisk acquired Schooner Information Technology, developer of the flash-optimized database software SchoonerSQL and caching software Membrain.[9]
In July 2013, SanDisk acquired SMART Storage Systems, a producer of SSDs for the enterprise market, for US$307 million.[10]
In June 2014, Sandisk acquired Fusion-io, a producer of flash memory for enterprise datacenters, for $1.1 billion.[11]

Awards and recognition[edit]

In 2014, SanDisk co-founder Dr. Eli Harari won the National Medal of Technology and Innovation from President Barack Obama for his innovations and contributions to flash memory storage solutions.[12]
In 2012, the Enough Project ranked SanDisk the third highest of 24 consumer electronics companies on "progress on conflict minerals".[13]

